Title: Radiant Creamy Concealer Ginger
Description: About the product: Ideal for all skin types, this multi-action formula lasts up to 16 hours, and masks imperfections, blurs the look of lines and wrinkles, and hides dark circles and signs of fatigue. The botanical blend hydrates, firms, reduces redness, and strengthens the look of skin by helping its barrier retain moisture. About the brand: Nars Cosmetics was founded in 1994 by namesake French makeup artist and photographer Francois Nars. Housed in unmistakable, matte black, rubber packaging, the line is known for its luminous finishes and bold, long-lasting pigments. Ingredients: Aqua (water), Dimethicone, Hydrogenated Polydecene, Propanediol, Butylene Glycol, Peg-9 Polydimethylsiloxyethyl Dimethicone, Glycerin, Disteardimonium Hectorite, Peg-10 Dimethicone, Polymethyl Methacrylate, Bis-butyldimethicone Polyglyceryl-3, Sorbitan Sesquiisostearate, Dimethicone/vinyl Dimethicone Crosspolymer, Phenoxyethanol, Isostearic Acid, Polysilicone-2, Aluminum Hydroxide, Maltodextrin, Trisodium Edta, Lecithin, Silica, Tin Oxide, Triethoxycaprylylsilane, Tocopheryl Acetate, Sodium Metabisulfite, Magnolia Officinalis (magnolia Officinalis Bark Extract), Tocopherol, Vitis Vinifera [vitis Vinifera (grape) Seed Extract], [+/- (may Contain): Mica, Ci 77891 (titanium Dioxide), Ci 77491 (iron Oxides), Ci 77492 (iron Oxides), Ci 77499 (iron Oxides), Ci 77163 (bismuth Oxychloride), Ci 42090 (blue 1 Lake). How to use: 1. Apply directly from the applicator, with fingertips, or with the #12 Cream Blending Brush. 2. To use as a highlighter, select two shades lighter than your natural skin tone, and place on the high points of the face. 3. To add dimension and contour, select two shades deeper than your natural skin tone and place in the hollows of the cheeks, on the temples, and along the hairline and jawline.

Title: Lash Princess False Effect Mascara Black
Description: About the product: The original lash princess has a big and bold sister with voluminous false lash effects! The conic shape fiber brush provides lashes with dramatic volume and sculpted length, just like false lashes without all the fuss. About the brand: Essence was started by Christina, a fearless entrepreneurial woman, who wanted to make a different cosmetics brand – a really fun brand that offers both great quality and excellent prices. Ingredients: Aqua (Water), Paraffin, Glyceryl Stearate, Synthetic Beeswax, Stearic Acid, Acacia Senegal Gum , Butylene Glycol, Palmitic Acid, Polybutene, Oryza Sativa (Rice) Bran Wax, Vp/Eicosene Copolymer, Ozokerite, Aminomethyl Propanol, Tropolone, Hydrogenated Vegetable Oil, Stearyl Stearate, Hydroxyethylcellulose, Phenoxyethanol, CI 77499 (Iron Oxides).How to use: Starting at the base of the lash line, wiggle wand back and forth, adding as many coats as you like until desired length and volume is achieved.

Title: Unlimited Double Touch Lipstick 103 Natural Rose
14-Piece Makeup Multi Use Brush Set Rose Gold/Black
Description: About the product: Soft-synthetic fibre bristles leave an incredible makeup finish and the ergonomic handle provides a comfortable grip. This versatile set helps to create a variety of makeup looks for your face and eyes.How to use Foundation Brush 1. For the first method, simply dab the foundation onto your forehead, cheeks, chin, and onto the bridge of your nose with your fingers.  2. Then, blend the product in using your foundation brush, moving in circular motions for a seamless finish.  Bronzer & Blush Brush  1. Swipe the brush into your blush or bronzer and tap gently to release any excess product. 2. If you're applying blush, sweep the brush across the apples of your cheeks, blending in circular motions to spread the product evenly.  3. For bronzer, you'll want to apply your product in the shape of the number three: start at your forehead, swoop down to your cheekbones, and then down to your jawline.  4. Repeat on the other side.  5. Then, swipe some bronzer on the apples of your cheeks and the bridge of your nose, too. Powder Brush  1. Dip it in or swirl across the powder (if you're using loose powder, you'll want to tap some product in the lid first so you can control how much goes on)  2. Gently tap off the excess product and swipe the brush across your face wherever you need it.  3. You can also use it to touch up shiny spots throughout the day.  Contour Brush  1. Dip the brush head into your bronzer or contouring powder and sweep it right underneath your cheekbones (in the hollow of your cheeks) or underneath your jawline.  2. Blend lightly, in small, circular motions, to buff away any harsh edges and to make the color look more like a shadow instead of a line.  Angled Eye Brush  1. Dip it into any brow product and make tiny strokes along your brows to fill in sparse spots and shape your arches.  2. Dip your brush into your eyeliner or eyeshadow product and line your upper lash line, flicking it out to a wing once you reach the outer edge of your eye.  Flat Eyeshadow Brush  1. Dip the flat side of your brush into your eyeshadow and swipe the bristles across your eyelid, starting at the inner corner and moving outwards.  2. Add another layer if you want a darker look.

Title: Nail Gel Polish Set Multicolour
Description: Introducing new False Lash X-Fiber Mascara, for our ultimate false lash look without the hassle of false lashes or eyelash extensions for lashes that appear lifted and longer. Extreme length, extreme volume, extreme buildability. False Lash Superstar X Fiber Mascara has a two-step formula. Step one is a volumizing black primer that thickens the look of each lash to build extreme volume. Step two has lengthening fibers enriched with 20X more fibers for extreme length.
